bas-cpp (1.0.1) testing; urgency=medium

  * Refactor volume backends into dedicated modules:
    - src/volume/zip (MemoryZip)
    - src/volume/fat32 (Fat32Volume + file streams)
    - src/volume/ext4 (Ext4Volume + file streams)
  * Add FAT32 image volume support and wire it through VolumeManager.
  * Add ext2/ext3/ext4 image volume support with optional libext2fs linking.
  * Avoid full-image buffering for FAT32/EXT file access by introducing
    dedicated RandomInputStream/OutputStream implementations.
  * Switch Ext4Volume to on-demand path->inode resolution and cache
    directory indexes by inode to avoid expensive full-tree mount scans.
  * Add Ext4Volume execution context primitives (uid/gid/groups + IUserDb)
    and enforce mode-based access checks for traversal/read/list paths.
  * Add image-based tests for FAT32 and EXT volume backends.
  * Update build wiring and includes for relocated MemoryZip paths.

